Phase 6: Live Internet Access (Web Scraping)
    What we did:

        We built a digital web browser for our AI.

        We gave the AI the ability to bypass website security and read Wikipedia.

        We extracted pure English text from the website to feed back into the AI's brain.

    How we did it:

        We updated our System Prompt to give the AI two JSON tools to choose from (get_weather and scrape_wikipedia).

        We wrote Python code to clean up the user's search words (replacing spaces with underscores)
        so the web links wouldn't break.

        We used a "Rule Override" prompt to tell the AI to stop acting like a JSON robot
        and speak normally once it found the data.

    The Purpose:

        To fix the AI's "Knowledge Cutoff" (an AI normally doesn't know anything about recent events).

        To make the AI fully autonomous so it realizes when it doesn't know an answer and
        proactively searches the live internet itself.

    Tools Used: requests library, BeautifulSoup, and Python String Slicing.

    Tool Usages & Examples:

        requests.get(url, headers): This is how our code knocks on a website's door to ask for data.

            Hard Concept Example: Websites use security bots to block automated code. We used "headers" as a
                                  fake ID badge. It tricked Wikipedia into thinking we were a human using Google Chrome.

        BeautifulSoup: A library that cleans up messy web code.

            Hard Concept Example: A raw website is full of ugly code, buttons, and ads. BeautifulSoup acts like a strainer,
                                  filtering out the junk so we only keep the <p> (paragraph) tags containing the real article.

        massive_string[:2000] (String Slicing): A way to chop up text.

            Hard Concept Example: An AI has a maximum reading limit (Context Window). If we force it to read a 10,000-word
                                  Wikipedia page, it will crash. We slice the text to only send the first 2,000 characters.

